---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="About" description="About Chris Dearnley and this blog">
  <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none dark:prose-invert">
    <h1>About Me</h1>
    
    <p>
      Hi! I'm Chris Dearnley, a developer passionate about building efficient, 
      scalable systems and sharing knowledge through code and writing.
    </p>

    <h2>What I Do</h2>
    
    <p>
      I work primarily in the intersection of development and operations, helping 
      teams build better software deployment pipelines, infrastructure automation, 
      and development workflows.
    </p>

    <h3>Areas of Focus</h3>
    
    <ul>
      <li><strong>DevOps & Infrastructure</strong> - Container orchestration, CI/CD, cloud architecture</li>  
      <li><strong>Web Development</strong> - Full-stack JavaScript/TypeScript, modern frameworks</li>
      <li><strong>Automation</strong> - Scripting, workflow optimization, developer tooling</li>
      <li><strong>Photography</strong> - Capturing moments and sharing visual stories</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>About This Blog</h2>
    
    <p>
      This blog is built with <a href="https://astro.build">Astro</a> and <a href="https://decapcms.org">Decap CMS</a>, 
      hosted on <a href="https://pages.cloudflare.com">Cloudflare Pages</a>. It's designed to be fast, 
      simple, and focused on content.
    </p>

    <p>
      You'll find a mix of technical articles, code snippets, DevOps tips, and 
      occasional photography. Everything is written to be practical and immediately useful.
    </p>

    <h2>Get in Touch</h2>
    
    <p>
      The best way to reach me is through the comments on any post (powered by 
      <a href="https://giscus.app">giscus</a> and GitHub Discussions) or by 
      opening an issue on the blog's repository.
    </p>

    <p>
      Thanks for reading, and I hope you find something useful here!
    </p>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>